text.text:
Surprised my 10 year old and took her to her first cat cafe today!

This place was amazing!!! We had so much fun snuggling and playing with about 20 cats/kittens!

Highly recommend the Felius Cat Cafe! This facility is a nonprofit animal shelter with a cat cafe and all the cats are up for adoption (no we unfortunately did not get another cat - our rescue cat Lucy would kill us as she does not like other animals). All the proceeds go to the medical care and food and supplies for the cats in the shelter. We will definitely be going back to support the shelter and cats next time we are in town!

I've been wanting to check out Felius for a while now and finally got to visit their spankin' new location. Booked myself a 30-minute play session and received so many kitty cuddles and kisses. My favorite was Olive, the one-eyed tabby cat who was so sweet and precious. ðŸ˜­ Jamie gave me a tube of Churu and immediately got swarmed by all the kittens. BEST DAY EVER! ðŸ˜»
This place is heaven on earth. The staff at Felius are so kind and take amazing care of the cats. Great place to hang out with some adorable adoptable kitties.

This coffee shop is cute and the mission is so honorable! The breakfast sausage burrito is delicious and so are the lattes. I get a hot or iced latte (depending on the temp outside), skim milk, and either caramel, vanilla, or a seasonal flavored syrup. A yummy treat with a nice cause behind it. Meet a friend or come alone with a book (or peruse the shelves here). A local treasure!

This place is hoppin today! Very fun drink combinations, delightful service, and sweet atmosphere with couches and comfy chairs and plenty of fun seating. A super neat place to sit and do a puzzle, read a book in a cozy nook, or meet a friend and catch up. I didnâ€™t try the food but it looks good. If you download the app you get points and money off!

Very cute coffee shop with an incredible mission in Lincoln!  Great menu of coffee drinks including sweet specials and all the classics.  They have several bakery items in a display case, I didn't try but everything looked great.  The shop has plenty of seating in a mix of tables and adorable couches and the walls are covered in bookshelves.
I visited on opening day and was still able to get a cup of coffee quickly despite the line of excited customers.  Amazing atmosphere and there's plenty of parking available!

The coffee shop is an inclusive place that offers meaningful and equitable employment for individuals with intellectuals and developmental disabilities.
